                                Command : EDIT

NAME
   edit - Edit sectors, ships, planes, land units, nukes or countries

Level: Expert

SYNTAX
   [##:##] Command : edit land <SECTS> [<KEY> <VALUE>]...

SYNTAX
   [##:##] Command : edit ship <SHIPS> [<KEY> <VALUE>]...

SYNTAX
   [##:##] Command : edit plane <PLANES> [<KEY> <VALUE>]...

SYNTAX
   [##:##] Command : edit unit <LANDS> [<KEY> <VALUE>]...

SYNTAX
   [##:##] Command : edit nuke <NUKES> [<KEY> <VALUE>]...

SYNTAX
   [##:##] Command : edit country <NATS> [<KEY> <VALUE>]...

The  "edit"  command allows deities to edit properties of sectors (confusingly
called <land> here), ships, planes, land units, nukes, or countries.

If you don't specify any <KEY> <VALUE> pair, "edit" enters  interactive  mode.
Editable  properties  are  shown together with their keys and values.  Enter a
key character and a value to change a property.  Hit return to finish the com-
mand.

You can also specify one or more <KEY> <VALUE> pairs as command arguments.  In
this case, "edit" just sets the properties, and  does  not  enter  interactive
mode.

SEE ALSO
   give, swapsector, Deity

